{"tid":796580,"cid":6,"subCid":0,"title":"[曼聯官方] 摩連奴 : 我地輸運氣","createTime":"2018-08-28T01:00:13.000Z","updateTime":"2018-08-28T02:11:03.000Z","uid":19552,"like":11,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":17,"replies":[{"pid":"b63e9f6ca6e74c5aae2288a1f24e797d55941d4b","tid":796580,"uid":19552,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-08-28T01:00:13.000Z","msg":"Jose Mourinho felt Manchester United did not deserve to lose to Tottenham Hotspur and made a point of praising his players&rsquo; attitude and togetherness during his post-match interviews.<br />\n<br />\nThe manager also thanked the &ldquo;amazing&rdquo; fans at Old Trafford and singled out Luke Shaw&rsquo;s performance in the 3-0 reversal, while speaking to MUTV and Sky Sports&hellip;<br />\n<br />\n&lsquo;We were really unlucky&rsquo;<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;We worked very well during the week and prepared for the game very well. By the strategic and tactical point of view, we didn&rsquo;t lose. We played very well, the players had a fantastic attitude and, at half-time, the score in my opinion should have been two goals different, minimum. We created more chances than in any match. We were really frustrated at half-time with the result but we believed that we were going to win the game. Then something changed the game a little bit and the score was 2-0 but the team was in the game. I&rsquo;m not saying that with one goal, we would have won or even drawn, but we were very much in the game and only the 3-0 smashed the mentality of the team. One thing is to lose at home and deservedly, another thing is to lose undeservedly, being the best team, having a fantastic attitude and being really, really unlucky.&rdquo;"},{"pid":"da5662909a1bb78fe0cc2a69239f9188b35fd3d3","tid":796580,"uid":18385,"like":13,"dislike":0,"score":13,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-08-28T01:01:25.000Z","msg":"<span style=\"color: red;\"><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\">Save Mourinho</span></span>"},{"pid":"2b545a19b871f2e7d321a8d7cc0